<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Senior lawyers criticise handling of case of Sikh activist held in India]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/nov/05/senior-lawyers-criticise-handling-of-case-of-sikh-activist-jaghtar-singh-johal-held-in-india]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T09:27:03Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7cbb550305c6d90f879b31bd2a4ec6c5f04efc26/0_329_945_567 /master/945.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9670d05bad92a058198b652f5c98c58a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Jaghtar Singh Johal&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;英国部长保证一名英国男子被监禁在 &lt;a href =&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/india&quot;>;印度&lt;/a>;将接受公平审判，尽管有证据表明他曾遭受酷刑和任意对待三名担任高级公职的律师警告说，他们已被拘留。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;为了纪念 Jaghtar Singh Johal 被拘留六周年，&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/ International/lists/tag/profile/ken-macdonald-qc&quot;>;KC 肯·麦克唐纳爵士&lt;/a>;、Elish Angiolini KC 和 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists /tag/profile/jim-wallace&quot;>;吉姆·华莱士 KC&lt;/a>; 已写信给英国外交部长艾哈迈德勋爵，要求他撤回最近有关英国公民将在印度接受“正当程序”的言论。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英格兰和威尔士前检察长麦克唐纳勋爵，以及分别担任苏格兰检察长和总检察长的安吉奥里尼夫人和华莱士勋爵表示，“如果诉讼程序已”，或者指控出于政治动机并惩罚言论自由。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Johal 是来自苏格兰敦巴顿的锡克教活动家和博主，2017 年在印度结婚时被警察抓住。据活动组织“缓刑”称，便衣警察在他妻子面前，戴上头巾，将他塞进车里并遭受酷刑。据称，印度当局似乎已采取行动&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/aug/23/british-sikh-activist-tortured-in-india-after-tip- off-from-uk-intelligence&quot;>;来自英国情报部门的举报&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;时任首相，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022 /jun/30/boris-johnson-says-india-arguly-detaining-british-sikh-activist-jagtar-singh-johal&quot;>;鲍里斯·约翰逊表示，印度政府任意拘留乔哈尔&lt;/a>; – 持相同立场的&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/may/08/uk-urged-to-act-after-un-panel-rules-detention-of-briton-in-india-任意”>;联合国任意拘留问题工作组&lt;/a>;——但政府自此以来一直被指控立场倒退。在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2023-09-12/debates/7F276961-9BC3-4940-8B8E-6CFD62294300/MrJagtarSinghJohal?highlight=johal#contribution-F9A70D37-4BB5-4AD2 -A742-DAA6227BF430&quot;>;9月份上议院关于乔哈尔案的辩论&lt;/a>;，艾哈迈德表示，英国不会要求释放个人或干涉另一个国家的法律程序，“在遵循正当程序的情况下” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在给艾哈迈德的信中，麦克唐纳和华莱士写道：“贾格塔的案件不可能采取正当程序，该案是基于在数天的残酷酷刑下获得的所谓供词。英国政府承认贾格塔对在审前拘留期间受到国家官员酷刑的严重指控，包括电刑、殴打、压力姿势和威胁要活活烧死他。为了结束酷刑，贾格塔被迫在空白纸上签名，随后当局将其视为“认罪书”。这是他继续被拘留的主要依据。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Johal 面临与哈利斯坦解放军 (KLF) 杀人有关的恐怖主义指控，该组织是一个被禁止的恐怖组织，据称他是该组织的成员。同行们的信中说，在他入狱的六年里，没有提供任何可靠的证据，并呼吁艾哈迈德撤回他关于正当程序的“不可持续”评论。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;9 月，乔哈尔的议员马丁多彻蒂-休斯指责英国首相里希·苏纳克在艾哈迈德写信后优先考虑与印度达成贸易协议，而不是释放他&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/sep/08 /uk-decides-not-to-call-for-call-for-release-of-briton-hold-in-in-in-india-on-terror-charges-jagtar-singh-johal&quot;>;表示政府不会要求释放他&lt;/a >;，声称采取这样的立场不符合他的最大利益。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乔哈尔的兄弟古普雷特说：“我兄弟的审判是一场骗局，总理和外交大臣都知道这一点。他们不会采取一切措施把他带回家，所以他们就找借口。六年来，无休无止的拖延，虽然检察官在没有提供任何可信证据的情况下拖延了整个程序，但贾格塔却在印度监狱里慢慢死去。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;外国联邦和发展办公室发言人表示，他们致力于“尽快”解决乔哈尔的案件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们补充道：“我们继续向乔哈尔先生及其家人提供领事协助，并一直直接向印度政府提出他的案件。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 17:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Boris Johnson and Scott Morrison join forces on ‘solidarity’ trip to Israel]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/boris-johnson-and-scott-morrison-join-forces-on-solidarity-trip-to-israel]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T07:54:28Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/97e86be4b067023ac9a0b0b68f808200522e4b55/0_51_1024_614 /master/1024.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=936064dfae062cba774ffdca7b3522bb&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;斯科特·莫里森和鲍里斯·约翰逊在以色列会见世界利库德集团主席丹尼·达农。&lt;/div>;&lt;p >;澳大利亚和英国前总理斯科特·莫里森和鲍里斯·约翰逊已抵达以色列，表示他们是为了在内塔尼亚胡政府与巴勒斯坦激进组织哈马斯的冲突中表达声援。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这是第一次10 月 7 日，哈马斯在其南部地区对以色列平民发动残酷袭击，造成 1,400 人死亡，这是自 10 月 7 日以来，澳大利亚政界人士对澳大利亚的访问。现任英国首相里希·苏纳克&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/18/rishi-sunak-flies-to-israel-for-talks-with-benjamin-内塔尼亚胡和艾萨克-赫尔佐格&quot;>;10 月 19 日访问&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当地时间周日清晨，两位前总理抵达本古里安机场，受到以色列前大使的迎接致联合国，丹尼·达农。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/nov/03/a -两国解决方案是解决以色列-巴勒斯坦问题的唯一途径&quot;>;两国解决方案是解决以色列-巴勒斯坦问题的唯一途径|黄英贤&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;达农称两人是“以色列真正的朋友”，并表示他们将访问以色列南部社区并会见以色列士兵。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;预计莫里森和约翰逊还将在周日会见以色列总统艾萨克·赫尔佐格。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;莫里森在一份声明中表示，他很高兴能与约翰逊一起表现出对以色列和以色列的声援。世界各地的犹太社区。&lt;/​​p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;注册 Guardian澳大利亚免费的上午和下午电子邮件通讯，供您每日新闻综述&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;“这是一个了解第一手资料的机会莫里森说：“我们必须坚守阵地，向那些逝去的人致敬，向那些遭受苦难并正在卷入这场可怕冲突的人表示支持，并讨论如何继续前进。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;总理&lt;a href= &quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/australia-news/anthony-albanese&quot;>;安东尼·阿尔巴内塞&lt;/a>;周三与以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡进行了交谈自最近一次冲突爆发以来，这是第一次。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴尼亚语 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/01/anthony-albanese-australia-pm-speaks -with-netanyahu-protesters-richard-marles-office&quot;>;当天晚些时候在新闻发布会上&lt;/a>;表示，政府仍然关注加沙的人道主义问题和平民生活，尽管他相信&lt;a href=&quot;x- gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/israel&quot;>;以色列&lt;/a>;有权自卫，“如何自卫很重要”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在前往美国和中国之前，阿尔巴尼斯表示他没有计划访问以色列。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www. theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/08/australia-to-officially-resume-use-of-term-占领-巴勒斯坦-领土-reversing-coalition-stance&quot;>;澳大利亚正式恢复使用“被占领”一词巴勒斯坦领土扭转了联军的立场&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;莫里森与以色列的关系早已广为人知。 2018 年 12 月，莫里森改变了澳大利亚的立场，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/dec/14/australian-government-to-recognise-jerusalem-as-israels-capital&quot;>;承认西耶路撒冷作为以色列的首都&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;作为总理，莫里森打算将澳大利亚大使馆从特拉维夫迁至西耶路撒冷，“在可行的情况下，支持最终地位，并在最终地位之后决心”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;澳大利亚 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2022/oct/17/australia-quietly-drops-recognition-of-west-jerusalem- as-capital-of-israel&quot;>;2022 年 10 月悄悄推翻了阿尔巴尼亚政府的决定&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia-Ukraine war live: Russian shipyard in Crimea targeted by Ukrainian missiles]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/nov/05/russia-ukraine-war-live-latest-updates-kyiv-volodymyr-zelenskiy-vladimir-putin]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T08:36:18Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/64c03ff6abc8688b78cd156cf4e1331ba42589a6/0_380_8013_4808 /master/8013.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=96673200710de370234dc9b4a999dde3&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;在俄罗斯与乌克兰的持续战争中，两名乌克兰士兵在巴赫穆特地区一所被毁的学校附近行走。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Osaka’s baseball underdogs hope one more win will lift curse of KFC]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/05/osakas-baseball-underdogs-hope-one-more-win-will-lift-curse-of-kfc]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T05:00:08Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/88fb4f61fbb4906d8adf8e2ccd980678a2bdbde0/679_30_4155_2493 /master/4155.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=76f6c8ff470ffbb5e25ea39149b3624e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;阪神虎队的主教练 Akinobu Okada 被抛向空中，球队庆祝 9 月份赢得中部联赛。 &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;上次阪神虎队被宣布为日本最好的棒球队时，他们的球迷通过跳入运河并进行“绑架”来庆祝，许多人认为这让他们的球队陷入了持续的诅咒之中差不多四十年了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，沉睡的日本棒球巨人被迫再等一天，等待有机会赢得他们的第一个胜利来消除厄运&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/ mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/japan&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;日本&lt;/a>;自 1985 年以来的系列赛冠军，在输给当地对手 Orix Buffaloes 后，确保赛季的最后一场比赛进入第七名，决定性的比赛。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阪神队在大阪京瓷巨蛋举行的 38 年来的第一个系列赛冠军面前从未接近过，山本喜信的另一场英勇投球表演帮助欧力士将系列赛以 3-3 扳平，并奠定了胜局。周日，在同一场地——欧力士的主场——有望成为经典。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;老虎队在日本最受欢迎的运动中取得胜利将在他们的家乡大阪引发疯狂的庆祝活动，尽管他们的球场、传说中的99岁老人&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/aug/22/japans-field-of-dreams-school-baseball-teams-vie-for-koshien-荣耀” title=&quot;&quot;>;甲子园体育场&lt;/a>;，位于邻近的兵库县。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阪神和欧力士，连续寻求第二个冠军，已经为这场比赛画上了一个诱人的句号。这是 59 年来两个大阪球俱乐部之间的首次日本系列赛。当系列赛进入白热化阶段时，老虎队喧闹的支持者在一个闷热的夜晚鱼贯而出，希望他们的等待能够在 24 小时内结束。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;1985 年，阪神队最后一次观看比赛球队在系列赛中取得胜利，日本正处于资产膨胀的泡沫经济的边缘，玛格丽特·撒切尔是英国首相，纳尔逊·曼德拉仍在种族隔离的南非监狱里。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一些球队的球迷追踪那年他们为获得中央联赛冠军而进行的过度庆祝活动之后的几十年。一些人不满足于穿着衣服从戎桥跳入大阪道顿堀运河浑浊的水域，还把肯德基创始人桑德斯上校的雕像连根拔起——他与该队那个赛季的明星击球手、身材矮胖、留着胡须的人有几分相似。美国兰迪·巴斯 (Randy Bass) – 从附近的一家肯德基外面把他扔进了水里。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;许多人怀疑他在老虎队球迷手中的粗暴对待给球队带来了诅咒，即使上校被=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/mar/11/colonel-sanders-japan-baseball&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;从运河中取回&lt;/a>;，去掉了眼镜和左手， 2009年进行了翻新工程。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在接下来的17年里，阪神队只取得了两次前三名和大量的倒数名次，直到2003年才再次赢得联赛锦旗。他们重复了这一点2005 年的壮举，但这个系列和《Nippon ichi》（日本第一）的头衔却让他们望而却步。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“已经过去 38 年了，所以当然比平时更加​​紧张” 河濑佑子（Yuko Kawase）是阪神队的粉丝，每个赛季会观看她的球队约 90 次，她在该系列赛前夕说道。 “但球迷们完全支持球员。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;24 岁的老虎队球迷 Masaki Yamaguchi 在电视上观看了周六的比赛，他表示山本的投球让一切变得不同。但他并没有放弃希望。 “阪神上次成为日本最好的球队时我还没有出生，所以我非常希望看到它发生。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;37696d3d1ecddd852617ebc1c97ddf2abde2746b&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https ://media.guim.co.uk/37696d3d1ecddd852617ebc1c97ddf2abde2746b/0_287_5630_3379/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;阪神虎队球迷在体育场看台上挥舞旗帜表示支持&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt; Figcaption>; &lt;span>;阪神虎队球迷在京瓷巨蛋举行的日本系列赛第一场对阵欧力士水牛队的比赛中表示支持。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：朝日新闻/盖蒂图片社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;来自大阪地区的两支球队进入了系列赛，这会让许多厌倦了关注东京读卖巨人队的中立人士感到高兴——他们得到了有影响力的保守派报纸《读卖新闻》的支持&lt;em>; /em>; – 状态的下滑并没有削弱他们作为日本棒球贵族的声誉，尤其是在首都媒体中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;巨人队在日本职业棒球的早期统治着统治地位，而当时的——成立于 1935 年的大阪老虎队被认为是日本的第二支球队。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但他们成为关西人民希望的避雷针。关西是日本西部地区，包括大阪、京都等主要城市和神户 - 以及日本其他地方的体育迷，他们对巨人队的霸主地位感到愤怒。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管阪神队没有取得成功，但对俱乐部的忠诚在日本催生了一种无与伦比的热闹球迷文化。当球队在甲子园比赛时，噪音可能会震耳欲聋，尤其是当对手的球飞过天空并进入看台以打出本垒打时。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;大阪市中心有大批警察驻守，这意味着有大量警察在场。如果阪神在周日的系列赛决胜局中获胜，那么不太可能重演运河潜水的滑稽动作。相反，这座商业城市，其人民为其&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2018/sep/30/osaka-japan-foodie-tour-local-cafes-bars-street -food&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;富含碳水化合物的街头食品&lt;/a>;和幽默感，将通过百货商店的销售以及酒吧和餐馆的降价交易来标志着该团队的壮举。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Jason Coskrey &lt;em>;日本时报&lt;/em>;的棒球撰稿人表示，阪神在日本系列赛（相当于美国职业棒球大联盟的世界系列赛）中取得胜利，对当地人来说将是一件“大事”。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“老虎队的胜利对于大阪来说将是一个巨大的庆祝活动，”科斯克雷说。 “老虎队已经很久没有获胜了，如果他们最终再次取得胜利，那么这个地区已经准备好爆发了。他们拥有庞大、热情和自豪的粉丝群。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着他们赢得锦旗的赛季即将结束，阪神球迷、球员和管理层已经实施了一项非正式禁令，禁止说出“yusho”这个词&lt;em>; /em>;（胜利），担心他们会因为哪怕一点点的过度自信而受到厄运。相反，他们将这一渴望已久的结果称为“are”（你知道吗）。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;只有日本系列赛的胜利才能让阪神长期受苦和迷信的支持者相信，上校确实被解除了。他们所能做的就是等待和希望。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https:// feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Over the glass cliff: female chief executives have shorter tenure than men due to crisis management roles]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/05/over-the-glass-cliff-female-chief-executives-have-shorter-tenure-than-men-due-to-crisis-management-roles]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T08:00:03Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/2bde60e3f43fee73dd730feafe7ea03ed6340681/0_32_5824_3495 /master/5824.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=71dfe1c9f7a071ca2cb505e88f575995&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;坐在办公桌前看着平板电脑的女性&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;女性经历“性别任期差距”，最新研究表明，在上市公司担任首席执行官的时间比男性短，这可能支持这样一种观点，即女性领导者容易陷入“玻璃悬崖”，导致她们失败。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;分析对全球 12 家证券交易所上市公司（包括富时 100 指数和富时 250 指数）的调查显示，自 2018 年以来，女性担任首席执行官的平均时间为 5.2 年，而男性为 8.1 年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;劳拉·桑德森 (Laura Sanderson) ，罗素雷诺兹 (Russell Reynolds) 英国负责人，这家猎头公司&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.russellreynolds.com/en/insights/reports-surveys/global-ceo-turnover-index&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;进行了研究&lt;/a>;表示，任期差距的部分原因是有些男性担任首席执行官数十年，其中一位已担任该职位 39 年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“虽然样本量太小为了变得有意义，我们还需要考虑数据是否可以支持玻璃悬崖理论，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/science/2004/ sep/07/psychology&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;玻璃悬崖的概念&lt;/a>;是，当组织处于危机时期时，女性更有可能被任命为领导者，因此她们的地位被视为更加不稳定&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;埃克塞特大学的研究人员米歇尔·瑞安 (Michelle Ryan) 和亚历山大·哈斯拉姆 (Alexander Haslam) 在 2005 年发现，在公司股价表现不佳后，女性更有可能被任命为董事会成员。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;现任堪培拉澳大利亚国立大学全球女性领导力研究所所长的 Ryan 教授告诉《观察家报》，罗素·雷诺兹的分析“十分稳健，并且补充了”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“如果女性更有可能在危机时期担任领导职务，那么她们的任职时间可能会充满压力，受到更严格的审查，任期也更短。 ，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/04/bank-cut -my-bonus-because-i-had-a-baby-says-mp-leading-city-sexism-inquiry&quot;>;领导城市性别歧视调查的议员表示，银行削减了我的奖金，因为我生了孩子&lt;/a>;&lt;/ p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“任期缩短可能有多种原因，因为危机时期人员流动率往往较高，因为他们被认为表现不佳，尽管在他们任职之前就已经表现不佳。任命，或者因为当事情开始好转时，男性会重新担任领导角色。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;玻璃悬崖并不普遍，她补充道，但进一步的研究在其他领域找到了证据。例如，2010 年研究人员发现，代表保守党的女性更有可能以更大优势争夺其他党派的席位。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;目前，富时 100 指数公司中有 9 名女性担任首席执行官。富时女性领袖 (FTSE Women Leaders) 的首席执行官丹尼斯·威尔逊 (Denise Wilson) 表示，性别任期差距研究“是一项重要内容，旨在增加英国富时 350 强和 50 强英国最大私营公司董事会中的女性人数”。研究”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“从英国的角度来看，我们做了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/feb/28/women-board-roles-uk- “最大的上市公司” title=&quot;&quot;>;女性几乎在每一个指标和措施上都取得了显着进步，”她说。 “但首席执行官一直是我们努力取得进展的绊脚石。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;首席执行官职位的流动率非常低，她说，这使得取得进展更加困难。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为男性可以在组织内享有更大的追随者——支持。他们可以遭受重大挫折并再次崛起。担任过首席执行官的女性往往会转向其他职业。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“人们往往很快就会在老板手下排队，但当这个人不再像人们想象的那样安全时，这种势头就会聚集起来”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不过，她表示有理由乐观。富时 350 指数董事会中的女性人数为 &lt;a href=&quot;https://ftsewomenleaders.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ftse-women-leaders-review-report-2022-v2.pdf&quot; title= ”&quot;>;现在 41%，高于 2011 年的 9.5%&lt;/a>;，任命女性“现在已成为常态”。 Russell Reynolds 在对全球 1,500 名领导者进行的一项调查中还发现，下属对女性和男性的看法没有显着差异，这表明他们作为领导者的效率是一样的，尽管女性被认为更擅长指导&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;桑德森表示，越来越多的女性在公司董事会担任非执行董事后转任首席执行官。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这种情况经常发生在男性身上，”她说。 “这表明，让更多女性进入董事会总体上也有助于让更多女性进入首席执行官继任者职位。我对客户说的一件事是，如果你的董事会中可以有一位非执行董事，他可以成为潜在的继任者，那就是很好的继任计划。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href= “https://feedx.best” style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Former Guinea dictator Moussa Dadis Camara recaptured after armed prison escape]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/former-guinea-dictator-moussa-dadis-camara-escapes-prison-in-armed-raid]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T17:43:56Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/412dc8767cab91ccd9bd6a83058bccf26a2af95f/0_196_4012_2408 /master/4012.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f6541936a2673b95c4d2a96b2fbfa5c3&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;几内亚前军政府首领穆萨·达迪斯·卡马拉上尉在科纳克里发表讲话&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;前总统军队和他的律师表示，几内亚 2008 年军政府在一名全副武装的突击队显然越狱后数小时被重新抓获并送回监狱。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;至少还有另外两名前官员与穆萨·达迪斯·卡马拉 (Moussa Dadis Camara) 一起接受审判。一位部长和律师表示，2009 年他担任总统期间发生的大屠杀发生在他早些时候的一次行动中，该行动在首都科纳克里引发了猛烈的枪声。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“穆萨·达迪斯·卡马拉上尉被发现安然无恙，并被带回监狱一名军方发言人告诉法新社，但没有具体说明被捕的具体情况。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡马拉的一位律师乔卡米·哈巴 (Jocamey Haba) 告诉法新社，他的当事人已重新入狱。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几内亚司法部长阿尔方斯·查尔斯·赖特 (Alphonse Charles Wright) 早些时候表示，格林威治标准时间凌晨 5 点左右，“全副武装的人员”冲进监狱，“设法带着四名（囚犯）离开......特别是穆萨·达迪斯·卡马拉上尉”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说边界已被关闭。目前尚不清楚卡马拉是否是出于自己的自由意志而逃脱的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;军队将这次行动描述为企图“破坏”政府改革，并向现任军方领导的当局宣誓“坚定不移的承诺”。&lt;一位不愿透露姓名的司法消息人士称，抵达科纳克里中央监狱的蒙面全副武装士兵宣称他们“是来释放”卡马拉的。消息人士称，在里面，这群人朝他的牢房走去，似乎已经知道它的位置。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;哈巴告诉法新社，他相信他的当事人被“绑架”，他的生命“处于危险之中”。 “他对自己国家的正义充满信心，这就是为什么他永远不会试图逃跑，”他补充道，指的是正在进行的针对卡马拉的审判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;赖特还表示，另一名这些人被从监狱中带走——此后被“重新抓获”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几内亚由&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/sep/06/guinea- President-held-in-military-detention-say-army-coup-leaders&quot;>;军事领导人 Mamady Doumbouya&lt;/a>;，他在 2021 年的政变中掌权 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://www. theguardian.com/world/2022/feb/07/contagious-coups-what-is-fuelling-military-takeovers-across-west-africa&quot;>;过去三年在西非和中非发生了八次&lt;/a>;。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;马里、尼日尔、布基纳法索、乍得和加蓬也由军官管理。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https ://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;颜色：橙色&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Revealed: plan to brand anyone ‘undermining’ UK as extremist]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/nov/04/plans-to-redefine-extremism-would-include-undermining-uk-values]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T18:10:46Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/740356ee2081d95028682ebc2ac77eb24655980b/0_59_5168_3100 /master/5168.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5ea5c20db42f8f61b0469c815fbab054&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;伦敦抗议者呼吁加沙停火&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;政府官员起草了极具争议的提案根据《观察家报》看到的文件，扩大极端主义的定义，将任何“破坏”国家机构及其价值观的人包括在内。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;新定义由公务员制定为内阁部长迈克尔·戈夫工作的他遭到了一群官员的强烈反对，他们担心合法团体和个人会被贴上极端分子的标签。将异议定为刑事犯罪”，并将严重压制言论自由。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一位白厅官员表示：“令人担忧的是，这是对言论自由的打压。这个定义过于宽泛，涵盖了合法的组织和个人。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;戈夫的住房和社区部于今年春天开始对非暴力极端主义进行审查。预计很快就会推出包含新定义的国家凝聚力和反极端主义计划。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;标有“官方-敏感”字样的内部部门文件称，拟议的定义可以“制定针对极端主义的新的、统一的应对措施” .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;它列出了一些它认为将被新定义“捕获”的组织。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其中包括 &lt;a href=&quot;https://mcb.org .uk/ce-bill-joint-statement-21may2016/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;英国穆斯林委员会&lt;/a>; (MCB)，巴勒斯坦行动与修补（穆斯林参与与发展），在一些保守党会议上发表过专题边缘事件，并于 2021 年向议会委员会提供了证据。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;文件指出：“极端主义是宣扬或推进任何旨在推翻或破坏英国议会民主制度、其机构和价值观的意识形态。 ”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据了解，戈夫的官员一直在与内政部和 10 号部门就该定义进行谈判，该定义是在一个特别令人担忧的时期提出的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;上周，内政大臣苏埃拉 (Suella)布雷弗曼将伦敦的亲巴勒斯坦示威活动描述为“&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/oct/30/uk-ministers-cobra-meeting-恐怖主义-threat-israel-hamas- “冲突苏埃拉-布拉弗曼” title=&quot;&quot;>;仇恨游行&lt;/a>;”，引起了许多自认为是和平活动家的参与者的沮丧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，在最新的亲巴勒斯坦游行期间，数千人聚集在伦敦特拉法加广场有 11 人被捕。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;民权组织表示，引入更广泛的极端主义定义将威胁言论自由。尚未就新定义进行公众咨询。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;这是对言论自由的无理攻击。&lt;/p>; &lt;footer>; &lt;cite>;Martin Bright，审查制度索引&lt;/cite>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Akiko Hart，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.liberty humanrights.org.uk/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Liberty&lt; 的临时总监&lt; /a>; 表示：“这一提议的改变将是鲁莽和愤世嫉俗的举动，有可能严重压制言论自由。”合法行使言论自由权，同时允许政府镇压他们不同意的社区团体、慈善机构或信仰团体。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Martin Bright，特约编辑，&lt;a href=&quot;https ://www.indexoncensorship.org/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;审查制度索引&lt;/a>;补充道：“这是对言论自由的无理攻击，并可能将每一个学生激进和革命异见人士定为犯罪。这从来都不是英国逮捕思想犯罪者的方式。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ilyas Nagdee，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amnesty.org.uk/giving/donate/give?utm_source= google&amp;amp;amp;utm_medium=paid&amp;amp;amp;utm_campaign=MAIN936T&amp;amp;amp;utm_content=amnesty%20donate&amp;amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw15eqBhBZEiwAbDomEh1W6bmIkew_FtJBsgHEJTCN9O5ViAcEAD_SPL4LgtUggDHS0V_Y1 xoCfRUQAvD_BwE&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;大赦国际&lt;/a>;英国种族正义主任表示：“这个定义必须不被接受或实施。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“极端主义的定义及其在[反恐战略]预防等反恐政策中的使用已经得到如此广泛的应用，它试图有效地阻碍人们组织和动员。拟议的定义更进一步，可以将任何异议定为犯罪。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府 2011 年 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukdsi/2015/9780111133309/pdfs/ukdsiod_9780111133309_en .pdf&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;预防策略&lt;/a>;将极端主义定义为“积极反对英国基本价值观，包括民主、法治、个人自由以及不同信仰和信仰的相互尊重和宽容”。过去十年来实施新定义的进一步尝试均未成功。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府在 2016 年女王演讲中提出了一项法案，旨在“应对极端主义的威胁”，并通过新的民事秩序制度来限制activity. The bill faced widespread opposition and was shelved after the government &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jan/29/theresa-may-counter-terrorism-bill-sinking-without-trace-extremism-british-values&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;failed to provide&lt;/a>; a legally acceptable definition of extremism.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Under the proposed definition in the documents, extremism would be the promotion of any ideology which aims to “overturn or undermine the UK&#39;s democracy, its institutions and values; or threaten the rights of individuals or create a permissive environment for radicalisation, hate crime and terrorism”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It adds that the definition should be supported with public guidance that enables “consistent use and application”. The documents state that “stakeholders have thus far agreed this sets a clear threshold for identifying extremism”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;There is significant concern among some officials because they consider the broader definition could be used against legitimate organisations fiercely opposed to certain government institutions or calling for their abolition. They are concerned a wider range of individuals could be no-platformed or reported as suspected extremists in official files.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2022/oct/24/huge-uk-public-support-for-direct-action-to-protect-environment-poll&quot;>;Huge UK public support for direct action to protect environment – poll&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The proposed definition also includes: “Sustained support for, or continued uncritical association with organisations or individuals who are exhibiting extremist behaviours.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It said the new definition moves from the 2011 definition of “active opposition” of British values to identifying extremism “through behaviours that enable the spread of extremist ideology”. This is a significantly broader definition, potentially capturing people who are considered to have failed to properly challenge what is seen as extremist behaviour.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Some officials are concerned the new definition could hamper the activities of legitimate political or environmental groups. It was reported in 2020 that at least &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amnesty.org.uk/press-releases/uk-deeply-concerning-peaceful-climate-activists-were-referred-dubious-anti-terrorism&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;45 activists were referred to Prevent&lt;/a>; over environmental extremism between April 2016 and March 2019. At the time Amnesty International described the referrals as “deeply concerning”. MCB said the government “needs to challenge its own extremists who are intent on dividing our communities”. Palestine Action said: “This new definition is clearly an attempt to undermine and intimidate our movement. We refuse to be deterred.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Mend has been contacted for comment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A government spokesperson said: “We are clear there is no place for extremism, and over the last few years we have taken action to tackle hatred and those who seek to divide us.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“As you would expect, we keep our approach to tackling extremism under review to ensure it meets the evolving challenge it poses.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘We need more women,’ says only female winner of Millennium engineering prize]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/nov/05/we-need-more-women-says-only-female-winner-of-millennium-engineering-prize]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T06:00:02Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d5b206a6b433ffae24b97fb34499efbfa214e60/0_106_2048_1229/master/2048.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=137a419a1e277c8812e5d1de98d05f4e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Frances Arnold won the Nobel and technology prizes for her work on directed evolution of enzymes.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;As a Nobel laureate, Prof Frances Arnold is not short of accolades. Yet being the only woman to so far win the &lt;a href=&quot;https://millenniumprize.org/news-articles/news/frances-arnold-technology-prize-winner-nobel-prize/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Millennium Technology Prize&lt;/a>; – the Nobel equivalent for engineers – is one of the least appealing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Nominations for the €1m 2024 prize closed last week, and the organisers have revealed that women formed just 16.3% of nominees, the highest of any year since the biennial award&#39;s launch in 2004, apart from the 28.1% put forward in 2022.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We&#39;d love to see more diversity in the winners of these prizes because we know that diverse people contribute to technology,” Arnold, an American chemical engineer, told the &lt;em>;Observer&lt;/em>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The award organiser, Technology Academy Finland (TAF), has pushed the scientific and engineering community to think about women when they consider innovations towards creating a better life.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Tim Berners-Lee was the inaugural winner in 2004 for &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/mar/12/tim-berners-lee-on-30-years-of-the-web-if-we-dream-a-little-we-can-get-the-web-we-want&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;inventing the world wide web&lt;/a>;, while others have been recognised for DNA fingerprinting, fibre optic networks and stem cell research. But Arnold said it would take time for more women to join her.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It&#39;s important to remember that these prizes are often recognising work that was started 20, maybe even 30 years ago, when women were not as numerous in the technology community as they are today,” she said. “So my prediction is that there will be more nominations for women because marvellous women are joining the technology community.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Also, it&#39;s possible women are not recognised as much because they work in teams. And these kinds of prize often try to pinpoint a contribution of one or a few – very few – individuals.”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/jun/16/womens-engineering-society-100-years-inventors-suffragettes&quot;>;Why the Women&#39;s Engineering Society still has its work cut out after 100 years&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Arnold said she was “thrilled” to have received the prize in 2016 for her work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://millenniumprize.org/winners/pioneering-directed-evolution/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;directed evolution&lt;/a>; of enzymes. “I&#39;m an engineer by training, and it&#39;s a huge prize for engineers – you can think of it as the Nobel prize for engineers. Two years later, I won the Nobel prize [in chemistry] – I don&#39;t know how those are connected, but it was for basically the same sets of ideas.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Winning took “a lot of hard work”, she said. “And taking the blows and standing back up again. You have to be willing to take the criticism and do the hard work. I never shied away from that. I certainly wasn&#39;t going to let someone else have all the fun. I love research, I love invention. Why would I let the men have all the fun?”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In addition to her research, Arnold also co-chairs President Joe Biden&#39;s Council of Advisors on Science and Technology and teaches at the California Institute of Technology.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Half of our undergraduates are women. So the pipeline is there. Whether they stay to compete in academic research is another question.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Women often choose to “look more widely” than men and often go into leadership positions in industry, Arnold said, where “maybe their potential for making these big discoveries is not as great”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Her own big discovery was that she could breed enzymes like others breed sheep or yeast. In directed evolution, unlike natural selection, enzymes are encouraged to mutate then selected by engineers for specific properties that are useful, such as for creating fuels, medicines, chemicals and consumer goods. Until then, most scientists had attempted to understand how each part of the enzyme worked so they could design enzymes.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It is similar to the black box approach of artificial intelligence, she said. “There are a lot of parallels with AI and not just generative AI, but with artificial intelligence. Because these are navigating complex problems. Engineering an enzyme is a tremendously complex problem where we can&#39;t sit down and specify all the interactions that are important in the design – nobody&#39;s been able to do that.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“So machine learning and AI are very good at seeing the important patterns. We may not perceive it in the same way that the machine does it. But the machine catches those patterns and can greatly speed up the process of enzyme engineering. I do a lot of AI work myself.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“They&#39;re both methodologies for traversing complex landscapes, we&#39;d say. And you can meld them. Evolutionary search is a very simple search process on a complex landscape. Machine learning can do it in a different way. And there are many opportunities for melding these processes.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;TAF is keen for more people to nominate women for its prize. Dr Markku Ellilä, the academy&#39;s chief executive, said: “The problem is structural and requires that women are encouraged to work in science at a young age. We aim to participate in this work through cooperation with universities and, for instance, by organising pitching contests for doctoral students and nominating candidates for Singapore&#39;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://gyss.nrf.gov.sg/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Global Young Scientists Summit&lt;/a>;.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The chair of the academy&#39;s board, Minna Palmroth, professor in computational space physics, said that progress was being made. “Within this nominations round we pilot-tested purely women-targeted content in our nominations campaign, which gained promising results. However, there is still a lot to do, and that is why the prize will continue to encourage an increasing number of women to be nominated in the coming years.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 15:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Three dead in firefighting plane crash in outback Queensland]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/queensland-outback-plane-crash-kills-aerial-firefighters-near-cloncurry]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T23:40:12Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7babc0daa2f55a9bf8a7d0a7b614d0da8a4e19f9/0_130_4000_2401/master/4000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=db2e2b3b780588142a90516c376d2998&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A generic image of police tape&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Three members of an aerial firefighting crew have died after their light plane crashed in remote north-west Queensland.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A member of the public raised the alarm about 2.30pm on Saturday, reporting the crash near a mine site north-west of McKinlay, near Cloncurry.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Police said a rescue helicopter crew spotted the wreckage and officers arrived on the scene about 5pm, confirming all three on board had died.&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;Sign up for Guardian Australia&#39;s free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) said the aircraft had been engaged to conduct line scans and was travelling from Toowoomba to Mount Isa when it crashed.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/QldFES/status/1720736306559697314&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;Our hearts are heavy following the fatal plane crash this afternoon in north west Queensland and the tragic loss of three people supporting our bushfire response. During natural disasters in Queensland, we respond as a family. That family includes those contracted to support our…&lt;/p>;— Qld Fire &amp;amp; Emergency (@QldFES) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/QldFES/status/1720736306559697314?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;November 4, 2023&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The Queensland premier, Annastacia Palaszczuk, and fire and the emergency services minister, Mark Ryan, released a statement on Saturday night expressing their sympathy to the family, friends and colleagues of the crew.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The three had been playing a critical role in saving lives and protecting property by their intelligence and mapping work from the air to help firefighters on the ground, they said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I am terribly saddened by what has happened,” Palaszczuk said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The crew on board this aircraft have been doing everything they could to protect Queenslanders.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I send my heartfelt condolences to the many people who have been impacted by this shocking incident.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ryan said the tragedy would hit the aerial firefighting teams hard.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“So many of them know each other, work together, dedicate themselves to the same goal, to keep everyone safe,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;QFES also offered its condolences to the crew members&#39; families.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Our thoughts and prayers are with the families at this time,” it said in a statement.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;QFES said the aircraft that crashed was the same type as one that is used as the lead plane for the large aerial tanker (LAT), used to fight bushfires.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Both the LAT and the lead plane will be grounded until advised by authorities.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Prime minister Anthony Albanese praised the firefighters&#39; bravery.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“All Australians&#39; thoughts are with the family, friends, and all who know the brave firefighters who&#39;ve lost their lives as a result of the fatal air accident that occurred in north Queensland,” he said on Saturday evening while on a visit to China.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We know the people who fight fires and stand up in emergency services, risk their lives, each and every day to assist their fellow Australians, and to assist the communities,” Albanese said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Today our hearts go out to them.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Australian transport and safety bureau said a team of investigators from Brisbane was preparing to travel to the accident site.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A preliminary report is anticipated in about six to eight weeks, the ATSB said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Queensland police are also investigating and will prepare a report for the coroner.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Murder charge after human bones found in burnt-out tree trunk in NSW]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/charge-after-human-bones-found-in-burnt-out-tree-trunk-in-nsw]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T01:13:27Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/1c02aa02fea5b65983393d1b4ecccecdeef16705/0_202_2332_1399/master/2332.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=2929bb345dbf89d1de65bc175ae0e19b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;David Collisson&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The discovery of human remains in a burnt-out tree trunk has led to a murder charge over a missing man who spent two decades in prison.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Police on Saturday arrested and charged a 33-year-old man at Maroubra police station over the murder of David Collisson.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Collisson, 53, was reported missing on 15 October after he was last seen at a property in Menah, north-west of Mudgee in NSW.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;His suspicious disappearance followed his release from prison more than two decades after he was convicted of the “cold blooded, callous and cruel shooting” of 17-year-old Shahab Kargarian.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Shahab and his girlfriend, Shabnam Faiz, 17, were eating takeaway in a park on Sydney&#39;s north shore in 2000 when Collisson, accompanied by another man, demanded the teen&#39;s wallet.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He then shot the victim four to five times in a robbery gone wrong.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Collisson pleaded not guilty to the murder and maintained his innocence throughout the trial and sentencing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The 33-year-old man arrested on Saturday was remanded in custody and will face Parramatta local court on Sunday, charged with murder and a number of weapons charges.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The arrest follows searches of the property where Collission was last seen. A number of bones, believed to be human, were found in a burnt-out tree trunk.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Police will allege in court the man fatally shot Collisson at the property over a dispute.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russell Brand sexual assault claimant felt ‘used and abused’ on film set]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/nov/04/russell-brand-sexual-assault-claimant-felt-used-and-abused-on-film-set]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T23:39:50Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/026284a419c9a46febebc2da999fc02bf88ea4aa/0_236_4608_2765/master/4608.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1a121424d9060b42cff73934eefb024b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A close up of Russell Brand wearing a brown leather jacket&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;An actor who claims the actor and comedian Russell Brand sexually assaulted her while on the film set of the 2011 comedy Arthur says she felt “used and abused” by him.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The woman, who has not been named, states in a lawsuit filed in New York state on Friday that Brand first exposed himself to her in full view of some of the cast and crew of Arthur, which was filmed in New York City.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;She further alleges that later the same day Brand entered the lavatories she was in and assaulted her “as a member of the production crew guarded the door from outside”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I felt used and abused,” she told the Sunday Times. “Disgusting is the only word. I felt like I was being used, that I was just an object for his momentary titillation.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The woman claimed there was a serious power imbalance in film-making, particularly between stars and those with smaller parts or extras. “Everyone usually turns a blind eye to bad behaviour on a set,” she said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“If I had come forward and said something to, say, even a production assistant on the set, what are they going to do? Are they going to fire Russell Brand or are they going to fire me?”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The legal case follows a series of allegations against the 48-year-old performer by several women who have accused him of sexual assault and inappropriate behaviour, claims that in some cases date back 20 years.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand has denied accusations made by four women in an investigation by the Sunday Times, the Times and Channel 4&#39;s Dispatches, and said his relationships were always consensual. He has yet to respond to the New York lawsuit.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Warner Bros Pictures, which distributed Arthur, has also been named as a defendant in the lawsuit, along with other companies involved in the film&#39;s production. They are accused of negligence and of aiding and abetting Brand by tolerating his misconduct on the set.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The lawsuit alleges that Brand was drunk during the making of the film and exposed his genitalia to the woman as he sat at a table staring at her, “openly and obviously in the presence of everyone on set”, including film studio employees who treated his behaviour as acceptable.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The woman says that Brand followed her into a toilet, where he again pulled down his trousers, then shoved her into a stall and forced her to perform oral sex on him.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 08:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>